x4freetext: The 9Be and 12C targets were self-supporting foils
prepared by evaporation.The 16WO3 target was prepared
by evaporating the oxide onto a thin carbon backing of
about 10 mu-g/cm2.The 9Be targets used for the 6 MeV
and 10 MeV exposures were weighed directly and found
to have surface densities of 37 mu-g/cm2 and
47 mu-g/cm2,respectively.
